1. What is PHP
- Server side web language
- first stood for personal home page (1995), but now stands for PHP hypertext preprocessor
- PHP can be embedded directly in your html code using code blocks
- index.php allows the command line interpreter to run the file
- // php code block

2. PHP Data & Structure
- variables in php start with the $ sign
- 
- 
- single statements do not rquire semi colons, but multiple statements or lines do
- comments //

3. PHP Datatypes
- ints, floats, strings, arrays , bools, objects, resources (files, query responses)
- gettype($one) // returns the data type
- a float operated on or with an int will return float
- $greeting = "hi"; $greeting[0] // returns "h"
- \n // new line
- $bool = TRUE
- $var_dump($bool) // prints the var and value
- zero values and empty strings are falsey values
- constants don't require a dollar sign as a prefix
- php has built in constants
- define("YEAR", 2014);
- $myArray = array('eyes', 2); 
- $myArray[0] // 'eyes'
- arrays can hold mixed data types
- associative arrays allow us to use a string as a key:
$eye_colors = array('chris' => 'blue', 'judy' => 'green'); // $eye_colors['chris']

4. PHP Operators
- an operator takes one or more values and yields another value
- +, -, *, /, ++, --
- ==, ===, !=, !==, >, =
- and, or, !
- . // period is the concat operator

5. PHP Conditionals & Loops
- if( ) { } elseif ( ) { } else { }
- for($count = 0; $count < 10; $count++) { }
- foreach( $icons as $icon) { }
